  <title>IDE support for PHP 5.3</title>

  <section xml:id="flow3.idesforphp53.introduction">
    <title>Namespaces</title>

    <para>PHP 5.3 introduced the support of namespaces. This is a completely
    new syntax in PHP which is not supported by most editors (yet). However,
    the following IDEs are known to be PHP 5.3 compatible.</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <title>Open Source</title>

      <listitem>
        <para>Netbeans 6.8 and above
        <uri>http://bits.netbeans.org/netbeans/6.8/m1/</uri></para>

        <para>Cross Platform: Yes</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Eclipse PDT 2.1 and above
        <uri>http://eclipse.org/pdt/</uri></para>

        <para>Cross Platform: Yes</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <itemizedlist>
      <title>Proprietary</title>

      <listitem>
        <para>Zend Studio 7.0 and above
        <uri>http://www.zend.com/en/products/studio/</uri></para>

        <para>Cross Platform: Yes</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>JetBrains Web IDE
        <uri>http://www.jetbrains.net/confluence/display/WI/Web+IDE+EAP</uri></para>

        <para>Cross Platform: Yes</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>You should install one of these versions, if you don't want to see
    all those red syntax-error-symbols in your php-files.</para>
  </section>
</appendix>
